AMEND S e n ate Bill No. 1454 House Bill No. 1429*
by deleting all language after the enacting clause and substituting instead the following:
SECTION 1. Chapter 81 of the Private Acts of 2014, and any other acts amendatory
thereto, is amended by designating the existing language of Section 2.02 as subsection (a) and
adding the following as a new subsection (b):
(b) To avoid an actual conflict of interest, the appearance of a conflict of interest,
or practice of favoring, providing benefits to, or giving any preference to a relative, no
individual shall be considered for any elected position if he or she is an immediate
relative to another elected official. The restrictions on elected positions established in
this subsection (b) shall only apply to electable positions for offices within the City of
New Johnsonville. An immediate relative of a state, county, city, municipal, federal, or
other official is not prohibited from being considered for an elected position within the
City of New Johnsonville under this subsection (b). For purposes of this subsection (b),
"immediate relative" shall include a spouse, parent, child, sibling, stepchild, stepparent,
grandparent, grandchild, mother-in-Iaw, father-in-law, sister-in-law and/or brother-in-law.
SECTION 2. Nothing in this act shall be construed to remove any incumbent from office
or abridge the term of any incumbent prior to the end of the term for which such elected official
was selected, as prescribed in Article XI, Section 9 of the Constitution of the State of
Tennessee.
SECTION 3. This act shall have no effect unless it is approved by a two-thirds (2/3) vote
of the legislative body of the City of New Johnsonville. Its approval or nonapproval shall be
proclaimed by the presiding officer of the legislative body and certified to the secretary of state.
